    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Overview\n\nIn 0.12 we have been more aggressive about backporting features which we're confident will not need backwards-incompatible revisions later. That allows the features to reach users much faster instead of languishing on master.\n\n## Problem\n\nUpdating `news.txt` always causes a conflict, which makes the auto-backport fail. This adds friction for contributors/maintainers.\n\n## Analysis\n\nThe current pattern is to update `news.txt` in both the master and `release-0-.12` branches. \n\n## Expected outcome\n\nMaybe the more \"ideal\" way would be to update `news-0.12.txt` since that's a bit more \"correct\".\n\nWe need a better approach that\n\n1. avoids merge conflicts (for backports), and\n2. avoids extra work for contributors",
